`of(a, b, c)` emits each argument as its own next value and then completes. `from(x)` takes a single iterable or Promise and emits each yielded value. Passing an array to `of` emits the array as one emission; passing it to `from` emits each element.

```typescript
import { of, from, Observable } from "rxjs";

const three$: Observable<number> = of(1, 2, 3);
const alsoThree$: Observable<number> = from([1, 2, 3]);
const one$: Observable<readonly number[]> = of([1, 2, 3]);

three$.subscribe((n: number) => void n);
alsoThree$.subscribe((n: number) => void n);
one$.subscribe((a: readonly number[]) => void a.length);
```

