A plain `Subject` has no memory; late subscribers miss prior emissions. `BehaviorSubject<T>` stores the latest value and replays exactly one on subscribe. `ReplaySubject<T>(n)` replays the last `n` values. For a theme selector you want new subscribers to immediately know the current theme, so `BehaviorSubject` is the right pick.

```typescript
import { BehaviorSubject, Observable } from "rxjs";

type Theme = "light" | "dark";

const theme$ = new BehaviorSubject<Theme>("light");

export const themeStream$: Observable<Theme> = theme$.asObservable();

export function setTheme(t: Theme): void {
  theme$.next(t);
}
```

