Refactor this RxJS v4 code to v7 idioms:

```ts
const subject = new Rx.ReplaySubject(1);
subject.next({ ok: true });
subject.subscribe(v => console.log(v));
```

In v7 you import named symbols from `"rxjs"` (no `Rx.` namespace), add an explicit generic to the subject, and prefer `.asObservable()` when exposing it.

```typescript
import { ReplaySubject, Observable } from "rxjs";

interface Status {
  ok: boolean;
}

const subject$ = new ReplaySubject<Status>(1);
subject$.next({ ok: true });

export const status$: Observable<Status> = subject$.asObservable();

status$.subscribe((v: Status) => {
  void v.ok;
});
```

```typescript
import { AsyncSubject, Observable } from "rxjs";

interface BuildResult {
  ok: boolean;
  artifactPath: string;
}

const done$ = new AsyncSubject<BuildResult>();

export const build$: Observable<BuildResult> = done$.asObservable();

export function finishBuild(r: BuildResult): void {
  done$.next(r);
  done$.complete();
}

// AsyncSubject only emits the LAST next() value, and only once complete()
// is called. Subscribers that arrive after completion still receive it.
```

Use `AsyncSubject<T>`. It buffers the very last value and emits it to every subscriber (past or future) once `complete()` is called.

```typescript
import { AsyncSubject } from "rxjs";

const result$ = new AsyncSubject<number>();

result$.subscribe((v: number) => void v);

result$.next(1);
result$.next(2);
result$.next(42);
result$.complete();

result$.subscribe((v: number) => void v);
```

`BehaviorSubject<T>` emits the most recent value to new subscribers the moment they subscribe; it's always live. `AsyncSubject<T>` withholds every value until `.complete()` is called, then emits only the last one. Use `AsyncSubject` for one-shot computations whose final answer matters more than any intermediates.

```typescript
import { AsyncSubject, BehaviorSubject } from "rxjs";

const async$ = new AsyncSubject<number>();
const beh$ = new BehaviorSubject<number>(0);

async$.next(1);
beh$.next(1);
beh$.subscribe((v: number) => void v);
async$.subscribe((v: number) => void v);
async$.next(2);
async$.complete();
```

```typescript
import { AsyncSubject, Observable } from "rxjs";

interface CompileReport {
  errors: readonly string[];
  ms: number;
}

const subject$ = new AsyncSubject<CompileReport>();

export const compileResult$: Observable<CompileReport> = subject$.asObservable();

export function publish(report: CompileReport): void {
  subject$.next(report);
  subject$.complete();
}
```

```typescript
import { AsyncSubject, Observable } from "rxjs";

interface Score {
  home: number;
  away: number;
}

const internal$ = new AsyncSubject<Score>();

export const finalScore$: Observable<Score> = internal$.asObservable();

export function submitFinal(score: Score): void {
